Silvicultural measures for prevention in risk areas: 
- adaptive management of fuel (fire load) at risk sites with increased vulnerability; 
- creation of forest fire strips (e. g., Combined with alpine pastures); 
- deadwood management (deadwood removal should be restricted to selected forests with high fire risk and be coordinated with nature conservation considerations); 
- fuelbreaks: in fire prone areas characterized by relatively frequent forest fires or where large fires can develop, such as in broadleaves and scots pine forests, shrublands and grasslands in the southern alps, or black pine forests at the eastern edge of the alps (difficult to implement on steep terrain, because of high costs of realization and potential risks of erosion or windthrow).

